From f018ae21fbad743e2feb2a69363d0b772e116d0a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2025 11:10:34 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL hostapd:Manage AFC Channel Change for
 Retail Mode

Currently, when AFC power events are received in retail mode, hostapd
handles them without a structured mechanism to manage channel changes
or payload resets.

As a part of AFC retail feature, introduce an API to read the wiphy
feature flag and determine if retail AFC is supported. Handle AFC power
events and payload resets in hostapd by parsing relevant NL events. Trigger
a random channel change to the optimal power mode upon receiving
the NL8011_WIPHY_REG_CHANGE event. Add a boolean flag
'afc_channel_change_pending' in the hostapd interface to coordinate
this behavior. If channel change attempts fail, transition hostapd to
the NO_IR state and deactivate the corresponding 6 GHz link interface.

These changes ensure that AFC-related transitions are handled
predictably and robustly, improving system reliability under
retail AFC conditions.

Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency: n00-001-hostapd-add-support-for-6GHz-operation.patch,
r65-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Fetch-AFC-support-from-wiphy.patch
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY

Signed-off-by: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
